1. Confidentiality
Definition
Confidentiality is the protection of information from unauthorized access or disclosure.
Why It Is Important
It ensures that sensitive information such as passwords, personal details, and financial records are only accessible to authorized users.
Real-World Example
When you log into your Gmail account using a password and Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA), your emails are protected from unauthorized access.

2. Integrity
Definition
Integrity ensures that data remains accurate, complete, and unchanged unless modified by authorized individuals.
Why It Is Important
Users and organizations must be able to trust that their data has not been altered or corrupted.
Real-World Example
In an online examination system, student marks should only be modified by authorized faculty members.

3. Availability
Definition
Availability ensures that systems, applications, and data are accessible whenever authorized users need them.
Why It Is Important
If systems become unavailable, business operations, communication, and critical services may be disrupted.
Real-World Example
An e-commerce website such as an online shopping platform should remain accessible to customers throughout the day.

#CIA Triad Comparison Table

Concept	Definition	Why It Is Important	Real-World Example
Confidentiality	Ensures that information is accessible only to authorized individuals.	Protects sensitive data from unauthorized access, theft, or disclosure.	Online banking systems protect customer account details using passwords and encryption.
Integrity	Ensures that data remains accurate, complete, and unaltered unless modified by authorized users.	Prevents unauthorized changes and maintains trust in the data.	A university database ensures that student grades cannot be modified by unauthorized users.
Availability	Ensures that information and systems are accessible whenever needed by authorized users.	Allows users to access services and data without interruption.	A hospital's patient management system must remain available 24/7 for doctors and staff.

